Joe Biden appeared to announce his candidacy for the 2020 US election, before immediately correcting himself. The former vice-president made the slip while addressing 1,000 Democrats at a dinner in his state of Delaware. He said his record was the most progressive “of anyone running for the United-” before correcting himself and saying, “anybody who would run”. The audience stood up and chanted “run Joe run”, while Mr Biden said, “I didn’t mean it!”  U.S Election: ‘It’s a beautiful day to vote in America’ –V.P Biden Us to Buhari: Force alone can't end terror Poll: Biden would outperform Clinton in 2016 general elections